How about something like 

> Be aware that pinning error reporting is governed by the same rules as everything else. If you have a pinning failure that tries to report back to the same host, by definition this will not work. 

@ptoomey3 Do people typically supply a separate host? Do reports go cross-origin? I forget where CSP implementations ended up, but I've had to use a proxy host in the past :sob: to get around this

Do you think it's worth supporting booleans on Strict/Lax? Like:

``` ruby
config.cookies = {
  samesite: {
    strict: true
  }
}
```

Use of a boolean on either would prevent a rule of any sort for the other enforcement mode. This could be checked via validation.

